                    <details>
                        <summary>How are player rankings calculated?</summary>
                        <p>Rankings are calculated based on a player’s top five performances at sanctioned offline tournaments, factoring in placement, event value, and recency to reflect current competitive form.</p>
                    </details>
                    <details>
                        <summary>How do these rankings differ from a game's built-in online ladder or ranked mode?</summary>
                        <p>Our rankings and a game's internal online ladder are both valuable, but they measure different aspects of competitive skill. Our system is based exclusively on performance in high-stakes, <strong>offline tournaments</strong>, which test a player's ability under the pressure of a live event. The in-game ranked mode is an excellent measure of a player's <strong>online consistency</strong> over a high volume of matches. We see them as complementary: the in-game ladder shows who excels in the day-to-day online environment, while our system focuses on identifying the world's best tournament performers.</p>
                    </details>
                    <details>
                        <summary>Why aren’t online tournaments included?</summary>
                        <p>To maintain competitive integrity and fairness, only offline tournaments are considered, as online results can be affected by connectivity and other factors.</p>
                    </details>
                    <details>
                        <summary>Can a player’s ranking change if they attend fewer events?</summary>
                        <p>Yes. Because the system emphasizes recent and top performances, players who compete less frequently can still maintain or improve their ranking by performing well in high-value tournaments.</p>
                    </details>
